"Here are the answers to the questions:\n\n***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\n1. Not very likely\n\nAt this point in the story, Bond has been caught by Le Chiffre's men and is being searched for any hidden weapons. He has been disarmed and is being held by the two gunmen. It seems unlikely that he will be able to escape without some kind of plan or help.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n6. Very suspenseful\n\nThis passage is suspenseful because it's a turning point in the story where Bond's plan has gone awry and he's been caught. The reader is left wondering what will happen next and whether Bond will be able to escape or not. The use of descriptive language and the quick pace of the action also add to the suspense."